Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.73,0:00:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely when we speak\Nto our brothers and our sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.65,0:00:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,our friends, our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.19,0:00:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems like everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.53,0:00:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is going through something stressful,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,something that’s causing them anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.99,0:00:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If it’s not us, it could be our mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.37,0:00:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a close friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.91,0:00:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.08,0:00:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be anyone that we’re close to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.21,0:00:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This causes worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.75,0:00:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It causes anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.46,0:00:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We get stressed out over the stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.13,0:00:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be like David.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.80,0:00:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What did David do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.43,0:00:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bibles to Psalm 18:6.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.10,0:00:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,David did not rely on himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.39,0:00:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned to his best Friend\Nand his Rescuer, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.94,0:00:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 18:6 reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.40,0:00:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“In my distress I called on Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“to my God I kept crying for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.70,0:00:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“From his temple he heard my voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and my cry to him for help reached his ears.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.33,0:01:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And verse 16 goes on to say in response:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“[Jehovah] reached down from on high;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“he took hold of me\Nand pulled me from deep waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.34,0:01:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“He rescued me from my strong enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.59,0:01:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,from those hating me,\Nwho were stronger than I was.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.10,0:01:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s comforting to read\Nwhat David went through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.89,0:01:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and how Jehovah helped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.06,0:01:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s comforting that Jehovah promises\Nto do the same for you, for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.90,0:01:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and for all of his loyal servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the past, Jehovah used angels
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.74,0:01:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—he dispatched them, he sent them—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.86,0:01:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to help loyal ones like Jacob,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.07,0:01:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Gideon, Daniel, Mary, and Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.41,0:01:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we still have angels helping us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.46,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But who does Jehovah use primarily\Nto help his servants on earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You, me, and our brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a privilege it is\Nto be used by Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.68,0:01:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be dispatched by Jehovah,\Nto be an aid to someone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.31,0:02:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But we need to ask ourselves:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.43,0:02:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Am I someone who is ready to be used?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.10,0:02:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Am I willing to be used by Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.40,0:02:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Am I willing to be dispatched
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when someone\Nis going through difficult times?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.40,0:02:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture, if you will,\Na young man swimming in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s doing fine until he comes into distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He begins yelling out to be rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.41,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thankfully, an alert lifeguard is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He dives into the ocean;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he plunges in\Nand brings this person to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.26,0:02:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, lifeguards are there for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re there to warn people of danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if they’re in danger,\Nthey pull them to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.97,0:02:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect that a lifeguard would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Jehovah expect of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.19,0:02:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he trains us to protect others
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.74,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be a lifesaver, a lifeguard,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for other brothers and sisters\Nwho are desperately needing help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way,\Nwe need to think about others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.79,0:03:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be observant like a lifeguard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.25,0:03:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and see if they might be drowning in sorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or in some sort of distress
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what we can do\Nto come to their rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.26,0:03:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And what can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow today’s text at Proverbs 17:17.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.89,0:03:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it in its entirety.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.68,0:03:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “A true friend
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.10,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“shows love at all times
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.15,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and is a brother\Nwho is born for times of distress.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.40,0:03:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“A true friend shows love at all times.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A true friend is not one\Nwho makes your problems disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A true friend is the one who won’t disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.16,0:03:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when you’re facing problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.42,0:03:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a true friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When David was going through\Nvery difficult times, many abandoned him
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.30,0:03:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—but not Jonathan, not Hushai.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.51,0:04:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They were there.\NThey were loyal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They were true friends\Nthrough thick and thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.81,0:04:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They were there to assist David,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to rescue him\Nwhen he needed rescuing the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they stood by David
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.11,0:04:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when he needed to lean on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.94,0:04:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Love was the very foundation\Nof their friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.90,0:04:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Love was enduring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.53,0:04:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Love was strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.37,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think about lifeguards,\Ngoing back to our illustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.04,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifeguards are not born lifeguards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They are trained to do so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.46,0:04:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be observant,\Nto come to the rescue of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is training us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to use that training to help others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be observant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.47,0:04:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be on the lookout\Nto come to their rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you think about true friends,\Nthey know us very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we don’t say anything to them,\Nthey are observant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They know if we’re going through\Na difficult time just by a look
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:05:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe our tone of voice\Nor possibly our demeanor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.99,0:05:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They come to our rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.08,0:05:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said at John 15:13
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.54,0:05:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that “no one has greater love than this,\N[and what is this?]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“that someone should surrender his life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in behalf of his friends.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.88,0:05:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know that our friends\Nare willing to sacrifice for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.47,0:05:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and at some point, sometimes it could mean
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.10,0:05:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would die for our friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But likely what it means\Nis that we are surrendering,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,giving up, sacrificing\Nour time and our energy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.44,0:05:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to the aid of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.69,0:05:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to build them up spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,help them physically\Nand sometimes even emotionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.32,0:05:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because love\Nis the very foundation, it’s enduring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It never, ever fails.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.54,0:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes we want\Nto come to the aid of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but we don’t know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:05:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t fix their problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t take it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.80,0:06:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can come to their aid\Nand be with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.01,0:06:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,be there for them, be at their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.51,0:06:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes just being a good listener
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.97,0:06:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s true love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The smallest act of kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.65,0:06:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth far more\Nthan the grandest intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need to remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.65,0:06:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Jehovah expects us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.16,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to be genuine and self-sacrificing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in our love at all times for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.12,0:06:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Unexpected events\Nhappen at unexpected times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to ask ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.17,0:06:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Am I ready to give of myself\Nand put things aside
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and jump into action\Nto help my brother or sister?’
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.35,0:06:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly,\Nthe second part of verse 17 says
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.77,0:06:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“a brother who is born\Nfor times of distress.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we to understand\Nthat part of the scripture?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it could mean a brother or sister
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.53,0:07:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who is our fleshly brother or sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but many times, it’s not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a brother or sister\Nspiritually who has come to our aid
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,—someone who is a true friend,\Nsomeone who is loyal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.29,0:07:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Proverbs 18:24 says,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘a true friend\Nis sticking closer than a brother.’
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the opportunity\Nto be used by Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.97,0:07:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be an answer to someone’s prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.60,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if we allow ourselves to be used by Jehovah\Nto make ourselves available
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and “dive in”\Nto come to the rescue of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And quite likely\Nwe’re going to go through a distressful time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll need someone\Nto be an answer to our prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.74,0:07:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A true friend is one who walks into your life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when others are walking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.08,0:07:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They enter; they come into our life\Nwhen we need them most,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.54,0:07:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,like the case of David.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.42,0:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We might be good\Nat coming to the rescue right away
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when something happens in someone’s life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.96,0:08:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But what would happen\Nif that illness or that issue
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is prolonged and it goes on and on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.22,0:08:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we still stick\Nto our brother and our sister
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and be there for them\Nin their time of distress?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we want to continue\Nto keep in contact with them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to assure them of Jehovah’s love\Nand our love by a note,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,an email, a text, or by visiting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these will assure them\Nthat they are truly loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.45,0:08:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When we think about Paul, the apostle Paul,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,he went through many distressful times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when he was in Rome\Nin the year 60 C.E., he was imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.13,0:08:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He mentioned by name\Nin the book of Colossians, in chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.26,0:08:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,five brothers\N—five friends—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that came to his rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They were brothers born\Nfor when he was going through distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they entered into his life\Nwhen he needed them most.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We recall they were called Tychicus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.53,0:09:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Onesimus, Aristarchus, Mark, and Justus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.45,0:09:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did Paul say\Nin Colossians 4:11 about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “They have become\Na source of great comfort to me,”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.71,0:09:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or as the footnote says,\N“a strengthening aid.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.34,0:09:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting that “a strengthening aid”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.71,0:09:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from a Greek word,\Nwhich is rendered “medicine,”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.47,0:09:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,something that provides comfort, relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Those five brothers, those friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,could not relieve Paul from his prison cell,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but they could be comforting\Nand “a strengthening aid”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.40,0:09:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he could endure\Nwhat he was going through.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.78,0:09:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They were willing to do whatever\Nthey needed to do to bring him comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be his messenger,\Nto provide material things for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.49,0:10:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,like clothing and writing materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.29,0:10:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a true friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,From his experience,\Nhe said at 1 Thessalonians 5:14:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.34,0:10:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“Speak consolingly to those\Nwho are depressed [or discouraged],
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.38,0:10:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,support the weak, be patient toward all.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That expression “support the weak”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,has been rendered\N“to hold fast, to cleave, to the weak.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of our brothers and sisters today\N—many of us—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are drowning in distress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.32,0:10:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re overwhelmed with problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.11,0:10:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,May we be observant;\Nmay we be willing to “dive in”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to rescue our brother and our sister
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—offering them a helping hand—\Nand hang on to them tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And may it be in our case\Nthat when we help somebody, they say of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.29,0:10:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“A true friend you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who showed love\Nin times of distress.”
